mibpnniSummaryAddrEntryTable.name: mibpnniSummaryAddrEntryTable
mibpnniSummaryAddrEntryTable.description: A list of mibpnniSummaryAddrEntry profile entries.

mibpnniSummaryAddrEntryEntry.name: mibpnniSummaryAddrEntryEntry
mibpnniSummaryAddrEntryEntry.description: A mibpnniSummaryAddrEntry entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibpnniSummaryAddrEntry profile.

pnniSummaryAddrEntry_IndexName.name: pnniSummaryAddrEntry_IndexName
pnniSummaryAddrEntry_IndexName.description: The name of this profile which is corresponding to the value of the summary-addr-index.

pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_Type.name: pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_Type
pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_Type.description: The type (e.g. internal or exterior) of summary being described.

pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_Address.name: pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_Address
pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_Address.description: The ATM End System Address prefix for the summary.

pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_PrefixLen.name: pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_PrefixLen
pnniSummaryAddrEntry_AddrIndex_PrefixLen.description: The prefix length for the summary.

pnniSummaryAddrEntry_Suppress.name: pnniSummaryAddrEntry_Suppress
pnniSummaryAddrEntry_Suppress.description: Determines what is done with addresses that are being summarized by the instance. The default value (e.g. false) will indicate that the summary should propagate into the peer group. Network Management will be able to set the value of this attribute to `suppress' (e.g. true), which suppresses the summary and any reachable addresses it summarizes from being advertised into the peer group.

pnniSummaryAddrEntry_State.name: pnniSummaryAddrEntry_State
pnniSummaryAddrEntry_State.description: Indicates whether the summary is currently being advertised by the node within the local switching system into its peer group.

pnniSummaryAddrEntry_Active.name: pnniSummaryAddrEntry_Active
pnniSummaryAddrEntry_Active.description: The state of this summary address entry.

mibpnniRouteTnsConfigTable.name: mibpnniRouteTnsConfigTable
mibpnniRouteTnsConfigTable.description: A list of mibpnniRouteTnsConfig profile entries.

mibpnniRouteTnsConfigEntry.name: mibpnniRouteTnsConfigEntry
mibpnniRouteTnsConfigEntry.description: A mibpnniRouteTnsConfig entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibpnniRouteTnsConfig profile.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_NodeIndex.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_NodeIndex
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_NodeIndex.description: Index that identifies a logical PNNI node.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsType.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsType
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsType.description: The type of network identification used for this transit network.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsPlan.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsPlan
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsPlan.description: The network identification plan according to which network id has been assigned.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsId.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsId
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsId.description: The value of the transit network identifier.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsInde.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsIndex
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIndex_RouteTnsInde.description: An index into the set of listings of connectivity to a given transit network from a given local node.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIfIndex.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIfIndex
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsIfIndex.description: The local interface over which the transit network can be reached.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsAdvertisingNodeId.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsAdvertisingNodeId
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsAdvertisingNodeId.description: The node ID of a node advertising reachability to the transit network.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsAdvertisedPortId.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsAdvertisedPortId
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsAdvertisedPortId.description: The port identifier used from the advertising node to reach the given transit network.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsRouteType.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsRouteType
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsRouteType.description: The type (e.g. exterior or other) of reachability from the advertising node to the transit network.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsPnniScope.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsPnniScope
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsPnniScope.description: The PNNI scope of advertisement (i.e. level of PNNI hierarchy) of the reachability from the advertising node to the transit network.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsVpCapability.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsVpCapability
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsVpCapability.description: Indicates whether VPCs can be established from the advertising node to the reachable transit network.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsMetricsTag.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsMetricsTag
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsMetricsTag.description: The index into the pnniMetricsTable for the traffic parameter values that apply for the connectivity from the advertising node to the transit network.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsOriginateAdvertise.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsOriginateAdvertisement
pnniRouteTnsConfig_TnsOriginateAdvertise.description: Whether or not the transit network specified by this entry is to be advertised by the local node into its PNNI routing domain.

pnniRouteTnsConfig_Active.name: pnniRouteTnsConfig_Active
pnniRouteTnsConfig_Active.description: The current state of this route TNS entry.

mibpnniNodeConfigTable.name: mibpnniNodeConfigTable
mibpnniNodeConfigTable.description: A list of mibpnniNodeConfig profile entries.

mibpnniNodeConfigEntry.name: mibpnniNodeConfigEntry
mibpnniNodeConfigEntry.description: A mibpnniNodeConfig entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibpnniNodeConfig profile.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeIndex.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeIndex
pnniNodeConfig_NodeIndex.description: A value assigned to a node in this switching system that uniquely identifies it in the MIB.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeLevel.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeLevel
pnniNodeConfig_NodeLevel.description: The level of PNNI hierarchy at which this node exists. This attribute is used to determine the default node ID and the default peer group ID for this node. This object may only be written when pnniNodeAdminStatus has the value down.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeId.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeId
pnniNodeConfig_NodeId.description: The value the switching system is using to represent itself as this node. If all the bytes of node-id are zero AND all the bytes of the node-peer-group-id are zero, then the value used for the node-id is derived from the node-level and node-atm-address. The derived value is that specified in the pnniNodeId object of the pnniNodeTable in the ATM Forum PNNI MIB.

pnniNodeConfig_CurrNodeId.name: pnniNodeConfig_CurrNodeId
pnniNodeConfig_CurrNodeId.description: The derived node-id value the switching system is using to represent itself as this node. This value is the value derived from the node-level and the node-atm-address.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeLowest.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeLowest
pnniNodeConfig_NodeLowest.description: Indicates whether this node acts as a lowest level node or whether this node is a logical group node that becomes active when one of the other nodes in this switching system becomes a peer group leader.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeAdminStatus.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeAdminStatus
pnniNodeConfig_NodeAdminStatus.description: Indicates whether the administrative status of the node is up (the node is allowed to become active) or down (the node is forced to be inactive).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeDomainName.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeDomainName
pnniNodeConfig_NodeDomainName.description: The name of the PNNI routing domain in which this node participates. All lowest-level PNNI nodes with the same pnniNodeDomainName are presumed to be connected.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeAtmAddress.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeAtmAddress
pnniNodeConfig_NodeAtmAddress.description: This node's ATM End System Address. Remote systems wishing to exchange PNNI protocol packets with this node should direct packets or calls to this address.

pnniNodeConfig_NodePeerGroupId.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodePeerGroupId
pnniNodeConfig_NodePeerGroupId.description: The Peer Group Identifier of the peer group that the given node is to become a member of. If all the bytes of node-peer-group-id are zero AND all the bytes of the node-id are zero, then the value used for the node-peer-group-id is derived from the node-level and node-atm-address. The derived value is that specified in the pnniNodePeerGroupId object of the pnniNodeTable in the ATM Forum PNNI MIB.

pnniNodeConfig_CurrNodePeerGroupId.name: pnniNodeConfig_CurrNodePeerGroupId
pnniNodeConfig_CurrNodePeerGroupId.description: The derived value of the Peer Group Identifier of the peer group that the given node is to become a member of. The derived value is that specified in the pnniNodePeerGroupId object of the pnniNodeTable in the ATM Forum PNNI MIB.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeRestrictedTransit.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeRestrictedTransit
pnniNodeConfig_NodeRestrictedTransit.description: Specifies whether the node is restricted to not allowing support of SVCs transiting this node. This attribute determines the setting of the restricted transit bit in the nodal information group originated by this node.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeComplexRep.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeComplexRep
pnniNodeConfig_NodeComplexRep.description: Specifies whether this node uses the complex node representation. A value of `true' indicates that the complex node representation is used, whereas a value of `false' indicates that the simple node representation is used.

pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_LeadershipPriorit.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_LeadershipPriority
pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_LeadershipPriorit.description: The Leadership priority value this node should advertise in its nodal information group for the given peer group. Only the value zero can be used with nodes that are not PGL/LGN capable. As we cannot be a Peer Group Leader in this release, this value is always zero.

pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_ParentNodeIndex.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_ParentNodeIndex
pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_ParentNodeIndex.description: The local node index used to identify the node that will represent this peer group at the next higher level of hierarchy, if this node becomes peer group leader. The value 0 indicates that there is no parent node.

pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_InitTime.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_InitTime
pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_InitTime.description: The amount of time in seconds this node will delay advertising its choice of preferred PGL after having initialized operation and reached the full state with at least one neighbor in the peer group.

pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_OverrideDelay.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_OverrideDelay
pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_OverrideDelay.description: The amount of time in seconds a node will wait for itself to be declared the preferred PGL by unanimous agreement among its peers. In the absence of unanimous agreement this will be the amount of time that will pass before this node considers a two thirds majority as sufficient agreement to declare itself peer group leader, abandoning the attempt to get unanimous agreement.

pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_ReelectTime.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_ReelectTime
pnniNodeConfig_NodePgl_ReelectTime.description: The amount of time in seconds after losing connectivity to the current peer group leader, that this node will wait before re-starting the process of electing a new peer group leader.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseHolddown.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseHolddown
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseHolddown.description: The initial value for the PTSE hold down timer that will be used by the given node to limit the rate at which it can re-originate PTSEs. It must be a positive non-zero number.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloHolddown.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloHolddown
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloHolddown.description: The initial value for the Hello hold down timer that will be used by the given node to limit the rate at which it sends Hellos. It must be a positive non-zero number.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloInterval.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloInterval
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloInterval.description: The initial value for the Hello Timer. In the absence of triggered Hellos, this node will send one Hello packet on each of its ports on this interval.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloInactivity.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloInactivityFactor
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HelloInactivity.description: The value for the Hello Inactivity factor that this node will use to determine when a neighbor has gone down.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HlinkInact.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HlinkInact
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_HlinkInact.description: The amount of time a node will continue to advertise a horizontal (logical) link for which it has not received and processed a LGN Horizontal Link information group.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseRefreshInte.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseRefreshInterval
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseRefreshInte.description: The initial value for the Refresh timer that this node will use to drive (re-)origination of PTSEs in the absence of triggered updates.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseLifetimeFac.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseLifetimeFactor
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PtseLifetimeFac.description: The value for the lifetime multiplier, expressed as a percentage. The result of multiplying the pnniNodePtseRefreshInterval attribute value by this attribute value is used as the initial lifetime that this node places into self-originated PTSEs.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_RxmtInterval.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_RxmtInterval
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_RxmtInterval.description: The period between retransmissions of unacknowledged Database Summary packets, PTSE Request packets, and PTSPs.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PeerDelayedAckI.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PeerDelayedAckInterval
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_PeerDelayedAckI.description: The minimum amount of time between transmissions of delayed PTSE acknowledgement packets.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_AvcrPm.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_AvcrPm
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_AvcrPm.description: The proportional multiplier used in the algorithms that determine significant change for AvCR parameters, expressed as a percentage.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_AvcrMt.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_AvcrMt
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_AvcrMt.description: The minimum threshold used in the algorithms that determine signif- icant change for AvCR parameters, expressed as a percentage.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_CdvPm.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_CdvPm
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_CdvPm.description: The proportional multiplier used in the algorithms that determine significant change for CDV metrics, expressed as a percentage.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_CtdPm.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_CtdPm
pnniNodeConfig_NodeTimer_CtdPm.description: The proportional multiplier used in the algorithms that determine significant change for CTD metrics, expressed as a percentage.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_InitTime.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_InitTime
pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_InitTime.description: The amount of time this node will delay initiating establishment of an SVCC to a neighbor with a numerically lower ATM address, after determining that such an SVCC should be established.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_RetryTime.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_RetryTime
pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_RetryTime.description: The amount of time this node will delay after an apparently still necessary and viable SVCC-based RCC is unexpectedly torn down, before attempting to re-establish it.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_CallingIntegr.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_CallingIntegrityTime
pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_CallingIntegr.description: The amount of time this node will wait for an SVCC, which it has initiated establishment of as the calling party, to become fully established before giving up and tearing it down.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_CalledIntegri.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_CalledIntegrityTime
pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_CalledIntegri.description: The amount of time this node will wait for an SVCC, which it has decided to accept as the called party, to become fully established before giving up and tearing it down.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_TrafficDescrI.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_TrafficDescrIndex
pnniNodeConfig_NodeSvccRcc_TrafficDescrI.description: An index into the atmTrafficDescrParamTable defined in RFC 1695. This traffic descriptor is used when establishing switched virtual channels for use as SVCC-based RCCs to/from PNNI logical group nodes.

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNet.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNet
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNet.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value localNetwork(1).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNet.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNetPlus1
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNet.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope localNetworkPlusOne(2).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNet.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNetPlus2
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_LocalNet.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope localNetworkPlusTwo(3).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_SiteMinu.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_SiteMinus1
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_SiteMinu.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value siteMinusOne(4).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraSit.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraSite
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraSit.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value intraSite(5).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_SitePlus.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_SitePlus1
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_SitePlus.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value sitePlusOne(6).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Organiza.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_OrganizationMinus1
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Organiza.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value organizationMinusOne(7).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraOrg.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraOrganization
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraOrg.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value intraOrganization(8).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Organiza.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_OrganizationPlus1
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Organiza.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value organizationPlusOne(9).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Communit.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_CommunityMinus1
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Communit.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value communityMinusOne(10).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraCom.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraCommunity
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_IntraCom.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value intraCommunity(11).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Communit.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_CommunityPlus1
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Communit.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value communityPlusOne(12).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Regional.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Regional
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Regional.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value regional(13).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_InterReg.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_InterRegional
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_InterReg.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value interRegional(14).

pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Global.name: pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Global
pnniNodeConfig_NodeScopeMapping_Global.description: The highest level of PNNI hierarchy (i.e. smallest PNNI routing level) that lies within the organizational scope value global(15).

mibpnniDTLConfigTable.name: mibpnniDTLConfigTable
mibpnniDTLConfigTable.description: A list of mibpnniDTLConfig profile entries.

mibpnniDTLConfigEntry.name: mibpnniDTLConfigEntry
mibpnniDTLConfigEntry.description: A mibpnniDTLConfig entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibpnniDTLConfig profile.

pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_NodeIndex.name: pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_NodeIndex
pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_NodeIndex.description: Index that identifies a logical PNNI node.

pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_DtlIndex.name: pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_DtlIndex
pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_DtlIndex.description: The index in the node's DTL table of this DTL stack.

pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_DtlEntryIndex.name: pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_DtlEntryIndex
pnniDTLConfig_DtlIndex_DtlEntryIndex.description: The index in the current DTL stack of this entry.

pnniDTLConfig_DtlNodeId.name: pnniDTLConfig_DtlNodeId
pnniDTLConfig_DtlNodeId.description: The node which is this hop in the DTL stack.

pnniDTLConfig_DtlPortId.name: pnniDTLConfig_DtlPortId
pnniDTLConfig_DtlPortId.description: The port from the pnniDTLNodeId to use as the exit.If the DTL stack does not care, this is coded as zero.

pnniDTLConfig_DtlLinkType.name: pnniDTLConfig_DtlLinkType
pnniDTLConfig_DtlLinkType.description: The type of link out from this node (pnniDTLNodeId).This is well defined even if the specific port is not specified.

pnniDTLConfig_Active.name: pnniDTLConfig_Active
pnniDTLConfig_Active.description: The current state of this DTL entry.

mibpnniIfConfigTable.name: mibpnniIfConfigTable
mibpnniIfConfigTable.description: A list of mibpnniIfConfig profile entries.

mibpnniIfConfigEntry.name: mibpnniIfConfigEntry
mibpnniIfConfigEntry.description: A mibpnniIfConfig entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibpnniIfConfig profile.

pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_She.name: pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_Shelf
pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_She.description: The number of the shelf that the addressed physical device resides on.

pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_Slo.name: pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_Slot
pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_Slo.description: The number of the slot that the addressed physical device resides on.

pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_Ite.name: pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber
pnniIfConfig_Address_PhysicalAddress_Ite.description: A number that specifies an addressable entity within the context of shelf and slot.

pnniIfConfig_Address_LogicalItem.name: pnniIfConfig_Address_LogicalItem
pnniIfConfig_Address_LogicalItem.description: A number that specifies an addressable logical entity within the context of a physical address.

pnniIfConfig_IfNodeIndex.name: pnniIfConfig_IfNodeIndex
pnniIfConfig_IfNodeIndex.description: Identifies the node within the switching system that the interface is directly attached to. The value zero is not a valid value.

pnniIfConfig_IfAggrToken.name: pnniIfConfig_IfAggrToken
pnniIfConfig_IfAggrToken.description: The configured aggregation token for this interface. The aggregation token controls what other links the link associated with this interface will be aggregated together with.

pnniIfConfig_IfVpCapability.name: pnniIfConfig_IfVpCapability
pnniIfConfig_IfVpCapability.description: Indicates whether the interface is capable of having VPCs established within it or not.

pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightCbr.name: pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightCbr
pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightCbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the constant bit rate service category.

pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightRtVbr.name: pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightRtVbr
pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightRtVbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the real-time variable bit rate service category.

pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightNrtVbr.name: pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightNrtVbr
pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightNrtVbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the non-real-time variable bit rate service category.

pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightAbr.name: pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightAbr
pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightAbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the available bit rate service category.

pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightUbr.name: pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightUbr
pnniIfConfig_IfAdmWeightUbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the unspecified bit rate service category.

pnniIfConfig_IfRccServiceCategory.name: pnniIfConfig_IfRccServiceCategory
pnniIfConfig_IfRccServiceCategory.description: The service category used for the PNNI routing control channel (VCI=18) on this interface.

pnniIfConfig_IfRccQosName.name: pnniIfConfig_IfRccQosName
pnniIfConfig_IfRccQosName.description: The QOS for the PNNI Routing control channel.

mibpnniRouteNodeConfigTable.name: mibpnniRouteNodeConfigTable
mibpnniRouteNodeConfigTable.description: A list of mibpnniRouteNodeConfig profile entries.

mibpnniRouteNodeConfigEntry.name: mibpnniRouteNodeConfigEntry
mibpnniRouteNodeConfigEntry.description: A mibpnniRouteNodeConfig entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibpnniRouteNodeConfig profile.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_NodeIndex.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_NodeIndex
pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_NodeIndex.description: Index that identifies a logical PNNI node.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeClass.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeClass
pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeClass.description: Indicates the service category with which this forwarding table entry is associated.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeDestN.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeDestNodeId
pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeDestN.description: The node ID of the destination node to which this route proceeds, and at which the DTL stack for this route terminates.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeDtl.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeDtl
pnniRouteNodeConfig_Index_RouteNodeDtl.description: The index into the owning PNNI node's DTL table of the DTL stack that goes with this route.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_DestPortId.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_DestPortId
pnniRouteNodeConfig_DestPortId.description: The port ID of the destination node at which the route terminates.A port ID of zero indicates the node nucleus.When the destination node is represented by the simple node representation, this value should be set to zero.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_Proto.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_Proto
pnniRouteNodeConfig_Proto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_TimeStamp.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_TimeStamp
pnniRouteNodeConfig_TimeStamp.description: The time at which this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the routing protocol by which the route was learned.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_NodeInfo.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_NodeInfo
pnniRouteNodeConfig_NodeInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route,as determined by the value specified in the route's pnniRouteNodeProto value.Currently not supportted and is set to 0.0.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_GcacClp.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_GcacClp
pnniRouteNodeConfig_GcacClp.description: For PNNI, indicates whether any advertised GCAC parameters apply for CLP=0 traffic or for CLP=0+1 traffic.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_FwdMetricAw.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_FwdMetricAw
pnniRouteNodeConfig_FwdMetricAw.description: The cumulative administrative weight calculated for the forward direction of this route. 0xFFFFFFFF means the metric is not used.

pnniRouteNodeConfig_FwdMetric1.name: pnniRouteNodeConfig_FwdMetric1
pnniRouteNodeConfig_FwdMetric1.description: An alternate routing parameter for the forward direction of this route. For information learned from PNNI nodes, this is the maximum possible cell rate (in cells per second) for the forward direction of the route. 0xFFFFFFFF means the metric is not used.

pnniRouteAddrConfig_IfIndex.description: The local interface over which the reachable address can be reached. The value zero indicates an unknown interface or reachability through a remote node.

pnniRouteAddrConfig_Info.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this reachable address prefix, as determined by the value specified in the route's pnniRouteAddrProto value. Currently not supportted and is set to 0.0.
